"{\"uid\": \"leaderlive.co.uk-news-24506019.jade-jones-dad-proud-following-olympics-heart-break\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PeopleFlintshire  THE DAD of an two-time Olympic gold medallist says he's proud of his daughter after she suffered a shock defeat early on at the 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 160, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jade Jones, from Flint, made history at the\\u00a0London 2012 Olympics, when she\\u00a0became Britain's first taekwondo gold medallist and achieved\\u00a0her first Olympic title as a teenager.\", \"from\": 162, \"to\": 336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 162, \"end\": 172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Jones-Hall\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.133662385767669e-18, \"text\": \"Jade Jones\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Jones-Hall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Jones-Hall\"}, {\"begin\": 179, \"end\": 184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9741892744659255e-14, \"text\": \"Flint\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\"}, {\"begin\": 244, \"end\": 251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9987323402906776, \"rank\": 0.0012692081528347136, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Flint's 'Golden Girl', took gold in the 57kg weight category aged just 19 -\\u00a0a performance which later earned her an MBE.\", \"from\": 338, \"to\": 458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 338, \"end\": 343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9741892744659255e-14, \"text\": \"Flint\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\"}, {\"begin\": 454, \"end\": 457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_the_British_Empire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.458219227192682e-16, \"text\": \"MBE\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_the_British_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_the_British_Empire\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She then retained her title in Rio four-years-later and, after a shock first-round exit in Tokyo, was\\u00a0bidding to become the sport's first three-time Olympics in Paris.\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 491, \"end\": 494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9778960516772348, \"rank\": 0.022603576612230357, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 551, \"end\": 556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999777307572354, \"rank\": 2.2208081335356444e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 621, \"end\": 626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999609694904, \"rank\": 3.903045506532462e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jones returned to the mat today (August 8) to take on\\u00a0Macedonian athlete\\u00a0Milijana\\u00a0Reljikj in\\u00a0the Women's -57kg events - but sadly fell to an agonising defeat.\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 683, \"end\": 693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macedonian_language\", \"score\": 0.6251044847970253, \"rank\": 0.5990609795799794, \"text\": \"Macedonian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macedonian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macedonian_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 31-year-old lost the first round of the best-of-three battle, before narrowly winning\\u00a0the second and drawing\\u00a0the third.\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 912, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That meant that the number of registered hits was\\u00a0used as a tie-breaker, with Reljkik securing victory.\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 1017, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That ended Jones' quest to become the first Taekwondo competitor ever to secure three gold medals in the sport.\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1130, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1063, \"end\": 1072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.98418341607729e-13, \"text\": \"Taekwondo\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her dad Gary, who watched on from the Mill Tavern in their hometown of Flint, said he was 'gutted' for his daughter, but remained 'proud' of her achievements down the years.\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1203, \"end\": 1208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9741892744659255e-14, \"text\": \"Flint\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TOP STORIES TODAY  Speaking to theLeader, Gary said: \\\"There was massive pressure on Jade to make history and I am\\u00a0really gutted for her that it did not go how she wanted.\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But, I am so proud of her regardless, she's had a brilliant journey in her life and done everyone proud with the medals she holds.\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Flint are so proud of her and what she's done for them.\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1611, \"end\": 1616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9741892744659255e-14, \"text\": \"Flint\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not think anyone will ever forget Jade and her legacy.\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She will be devastated but I can not\\u00a0wait to get her home now.\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1789, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She used to be known to me as Jade, but now I will always know her as Jade Jones and a lot of people will as well.\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1862, \"end\": 1872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Jones-Hall\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.133662385767669e-18, \"text\": \"Jade Jones\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Jones-Hall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Jones-Hall\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Love you to bits my superstar, you will always be at the top of the mountain for me.\\\"\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 1992, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jade was introduced to Taekwondo by her grandfather at aged eight.\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2017, \"end\": 2026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.98418341607729e-13, \"text\": \"Taekwondo\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She left school aged 16 to practice the sport full-time with success coming quickly.\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Known as 'The Head Hunter' due to her performance for scoring via kicks to the head.\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2231, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her hometown of Flint proudly cheered her on today with watch along parties\\u00a0being held in local pubs such as the Mill Tavern and the George and Dragon.\", \"from\": 2233, \"to\": 2384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2249, \"end\": 2254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9741892744659255e-14, \"text\": \"Flint\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flint\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This website and associated newspapers adhere to the Independent Press Standards Organisation's     Editors' Code of Practice.\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2512, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you have a complaint about the editorial content which relates to     inaccuracy or intrusion, then pleasecontact the editor here.\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2646, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you are dissatisfied with the response provided you cancontact IPSO here  \\u00a9 2001-2025.\", \"from\": 2651, \"to\": 2740, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Leaderis owned and operated by Newsquest Media Group Ltd, an audited local newspaper network.\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2776, \"end\": 2801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newsquest\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Newsquest Media Group Ltd\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newsquest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newsquest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Visitnewsquest.co.ukto view ourpoliciesandterms.\", \"from\": 2840, \"to\": 2888, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Echo Building, 18 Albert Road, Bournemouth, England BH1 1BZ.\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 2954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2890, \"end\": 2898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southern_Daily_Echo\", \"score\": 0.9999881270641688, \"rank\": 1.187